## Example: select/drop columns

`selectors` include their own `select` method, which takes a dataframe and selector:

::: {#5a345aa3 .cell execution_count=3}
``` {.python .cell-code}
df = pd.DataFrame({
    "age": [25, 30, 35],
    "name": ["Alice", None, "Charlie"],
    "city": ["NYC", "LA", "Chicago"]
})

selector = s.string()
s.select(df, selector)
```

